#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:6
msgctxt "description"
msgid "Qgoda basically copies files for deployment, optionally cooking the content with processor plug-ins."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:8
msgid ""
"Qgoda's general mode of operation is very similar to other static site \n"
"generators for example [Jekyll](https://jekyllrb.com/) or [Hugo](https://gohugo.io/).  It recursively copies all files\n"
"it finds from the source directory (configuration variable `C:srcdir`) into\n"
"the destination directory `P:_site` (configuration variable `C:site`).  The\n"
"destination directory is usually the document root of a web server.  Files \n"
"enhanced by additional meta information found in front matter are piped through\n"
"configurable chains of processor plug-ins."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:16
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"---\n"
"title: The Importance of Being Awesome\n"
"description: Everything has to be awesome.\n"
"---\n"
"## About Awesomeness"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:23
msgid "This blog post is about being awesome.\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:26
msgid "The part between the two lines consisting of `---` is the front matter as [YAML](https://www.yaml.org/)."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:28
msgid "## Asset Selection"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:30
msgid ""
"Files to be copied are selected using a simple naming convention.  All files\n"
"or directories starting with an underscore (`P:_site`, `P:_include`, `P:_views`,\n"
"...) are ignored, everything else gets copied."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:34
msgid "## What are Assets?"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:36
msgid ""
"All files selected for copying are referred to as *assets* in Qgoda.  Files\n"
"enriched with additional meta information in the document front matter are\n"
"conventionally called *cooked content*, *cooked assets* or\n"
"simply *documents*.  Unqualified content is called *raw*."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:41
msgid "## Default Processor Chain"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:43
msgid "Documents are generally processed in two passes in Qgoda."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:45
msgid "### Pass 1 - Markdown"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:47
msgid "[% TAGS [- -] %]"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:49
msgid "In the first pass, your markdown input files are converted to HTML with a Markdown processor:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:51
msgid ""
"```markdown\n"
"---\n"
"title: About Me\n"
"---\n"
"## About Me"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:57
msgid "I am *here*.\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:60
msgid "That will result in the following HTML code:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:62
msgid "```html\n"
"<h2>About Me</h2>"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:65
msgid "<p>I am <em>here</em>.</p>\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:68
msgid "The front matter is stored as meta information and not directly rendered."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:70
msgid "### Pass 2 - HTML Wrapping with Template Toolkit"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:72
msgid "The current output is still an incomplete HTML document.  It will almost always be *wrapped* into a complete document with the [Template Toolkit](http://www.template-toolkit.org/) using a *view template*, by default `_views/default.html`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:74
msgid ""
"```tt2\n"
"<!doctype html>\n"
"<html>\n"
"  <head>\n"
"    <title>[% asset.title | html %]</title>\n"
"  </head>\n"
"  <body>\n"
"    <h1>[% asset.title | html %]</title>\n"
"    <div>\n"
"      [% asset.content %]\n"
"    </div>\n"
"  </body>\n"
"</html>\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:89
msgid "Everything between `[% ... %]` is template syntax.  `[% asset.content %]` is the result of pass 1, the markdown content transformed to HTML, while `[% asset.title %]` is the document title.  It it is a good idea to pipe it through the `html` filter so that special characters get properly escaped."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/mode-of-operation.md:91
msgid "In reality, the default chain is slightly more complex but the details of it are most of the time not important for you.  In general, everything follows the Do-What-I-Mean™ paradigm."
msgstr ""

