#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:14
msgid "## Global Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:16
msgid "A typical multilanguage configuration in `P:_config.yaml` looks like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:18
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"linguas: [en-us, bg, de]\n"
"po:\n"
"  textdomain: net.qgoda.www\n"
"  msgid_bugs_address: Guido Flohr <guido.flohr@cantanea.com>\n"
"  copyright_holder: cantanea EOOD <http://www.cantanea.com/>\n"
"  reload: 1\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:27
msgid "### `linguas`"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:29
msgid "This is a list of language identifiers complying to [RFC4647 section 2.1](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4647#section-2.1) but without any asterisk (`*`) characters. An asterisk would not make sense here anyway."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:31
msgid "The first language is the default language of your site."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:33
msgid "The variable is mandatory!"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:35
msgid "### `po.textdomain`"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:37
msgid "An arbitrary identifier for your website. The only restriction is that it has to be a valid filename for your operating system. Popular choices are the reverse hostname of your site (like `net.qgoda.www`) or just a simple string like `messages`. It really doesn't matter much."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:39
msgid "This variable is also mandatory."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:41
msgid "### `po.msgid_bugs_address`"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:43
msgid "An address where translators should report problems with the original text to translate. The variable is optional."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:45
msgid "### `po.copyright_holder`"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:47
msgid "The copyright holder of the original content. The variable is optional."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:49
msgid "### `po.reload`"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:51
msgid "Set to 1 if you want translations to be immediately visible after they have been compiled into `.mo` files."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:53
msgid "Normally translations are loaded only, when Qgoda starts and then cached. Setting `C:po.reload` to 1 results in a little performance penalty but may be useful while you are translating the site."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:55
msgid "### `po.md_extra`"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:57
msgid "A list of [file name patterns]([@ q.llink(name='pattern-lists') @]) for additional markdown files. By default, all documents with front matter are potentially considered translatable. If your site has other markdown files that should also be searched, you can list them here."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:59
msgid "This variable is optional and rarely used."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:61
msgid "### `po.views`"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:63
msgid "A list of [file name patterns]([@ q.llink(name='pattern-lists') @]) for template files to search for translatable strings. It defaults to just `P:_views` or whatever the configuration variable `C:path.views` points to."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:65
msgid "### `po.xgettext_tt2`"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:67
msgid "The location of the `xgettext_tt2` program if it is not in `$PATH`. The `xgettext_tt2` ships with [Template-Plugin-Gettext](https://github.com/template-plugin-gettext) which is automatically installed with Qgoda."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:69
msgid "### `po.xgettext`"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:71
msgid "The location of the `xgettext` program if it is not in `$PATH`. The `xgettext` program is normally installed as part of a software package called `gettext` or `gettext-tools`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:73
msgid "### `po.msgfmt`"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:75
#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:79
msgid "The location of the `msgmerge` program if it is not in `$PATH`. The `msgmerge` program is normally installed as part of a software package called `gettext` or `gettext-tools`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:77
msgid "### `po.msgmerge`"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:81
msgid "### `po.qgoda`"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:83
msgid "The location of the `qgoda` program if it is not in `$PATH`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:85
msgid "### `po.from_code`"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:87
msgid "The character set of your content, defaults to `utf-8`. Setting this variable to anything else but `utf-8` is a recipie for trouble."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:89
msgid "## Configuring the Document Language"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:91
msgid "Qgoda has to know which language a particular document is written in. This means in practice that you have to set the `V:asset.lingua` to an appropriate value, that is a language identifier complying to [RFC4647 section 2.1](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4647#section-2.1) but without any asterisk (`*`) characters."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:93
msgid "You have several options to set `V:asset.lingua`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:95
msgid "### Per Document"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:97
msgid "You can set the language in the document front matter:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:99
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"---\n"
"title: Kalevala\n"
"lingua: fi\n"
"name: kalevala\n"
"---\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:107
msgid "### Per Directory/Pattern"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:109
msgid "You can save typing by specifying defaults for `V:asset.lingua` in the global configuration file `P:_config.yaml`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:111
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"defaults:\n"
"  - files: \n"
"      - /en\n"
"      - *.en.md\n"
"    values:\n"
"      lingua: en\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:120
msgid "This would set `V:asset.lingua` to `en` for all files in the top-level directory `/en` and addtionally for all files that have names ending in `.en.md`. See [@ q.lanchor(name='defaults') @] and [@ q.lanchor(name='pattern-lists') @] for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:122
msgid "## Language-Independent Identifier `asset.name`"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:124
msgid "All language variants of the same content should share a common property that acts as a link between them. Although you are free to use any variable name you like, `V:asset.name` is used throughout this documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:126
msgid "For obvious reasons, this identifier will always be configured in the document front matter."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:128
msgid "Take for example a markdown file `special-relativity.md`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:130
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"---\n"
"title: Special Relativity\n"
"lingua: en\n"
"name: special-relativity\n"
"...\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:138
msgid "If the German translation of that file is `spezielle-relativitaetstheorie.md`, that translation's front matter will look like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:140
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"---\n"
"title: Spezielle Relativitätstheorie\n"
"lingua: de\n"
"name: special-relativity\n"
"...\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:148
msgid "Both documents are alternate versions of the same content. They differ in the property `V:asset.lingua` but they share a common  value for the  `V:asset.name` property."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:150
msgid "Now it is trivial to link from the English version of that document to the German version:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:152
msgid ""
"```tt2\n"
"<a href=\"[% q.link(name=asset.name lingua='fr') %]>German version</a>\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:156
msgid "And you can link from other documents to the document about Einstein's special relativity regardless of the language like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:158
msgid ""
"```tt2\n"
"See [% q.anchor(name='special-relativity' lingua=asset.lingua) %]!\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:162
msgid "And since you almost always want to link to documents in the same language as the current one, there is a shortcut version for the above:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:164
msgid ""
"```tt2\n"
"See [% q.lanchor(name='special-relativity') %]!\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:168
msgid "By using `M:q.lanchor()` instead of `M:q.anchor()` you can omit the `lingua` parameter as it is implied. See [@ q.lanchor(name='referencing-languages') @] for more information about this."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:170
msgid "## File and Directory Structure"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:172
msgid "There are many different conventions for the directory structure and the file names on internationalized sites:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:174
msgid ""
"* You can use per-language top-level directories like `/en`, `/de`, `/fr` and\n"
"  so on. This is a simple and robust approach.\n"
"* Especially, when you are doing [content negotiation](#content-negotiation) with the [apache](http://httpd.apache.org/), web server you may consider encoding the language into the filename.  You would then not name your documents `index.html` but for example `index.html.en` or even `index.en.html`.\n"
"* You can also make do with encoding the language into the filename or directory of the output document. Qgoda will assist you with this approach by issuing a warning if one document overwrites another."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:179
msgid "## The Home Page"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:181
msgid "In a multilingual site, every document can be available in one or more languages. Unfortunately, there is only one `/index.html` and therefore the sites home page or start page can exist in only one language."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:183
msgid "One way to solve this problem is to use your site's default language for `/index.html`.  But there are smarter options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:185
msgid "You can use JavaScript to determine the user's preferred language and redirect them:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:187
msgid ""
"```html;line-numbers\n"
"---\n"
"location: index.html\n"
"view: raw\n"
"---\n"
"<!DOCTYPE html>\n"
"<html>\n"
"  <head>\n"
"    <title>Qgoda Static Site Generator</title>\n"
"  </head>\n"
"  <body>\n"
"<script>\n"
"    var lingua,\n"
"        default_lingua = '[% config.linguas.0 %]',\n"
"        supported = {};\n"
"    [% FOREACH lingua IN config.linguas %]\n"
"        supported['[% lingua %]'] = true;\n"
"    [% END %]"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:206
msgid ""
"for (i = 0;  \n"
"         navigator.languages != null && i < navigator.languages.length; \n"
"         ++i) {\n"
"        var lang = navigator.languages[i].substr(0, 2);\n"
"        if (supported[lang]) {\n"
"            lingua = lang;\n"
"        }\n"
"    }"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:215
msgid ""
"if (lingua == null) {\n"
"        lingua = navigator.language || navigator.userLanguage;\n"
"        if (lingua != null) {\n"
"            lingua = lingua.substr(0, 2);\n"
"        }\n"
"    }"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:222
msgid "if (!supported[lingua])\n"
"        lingua = default_lingua;"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:225
msgid ""
"// This is based on the assumption that the start URI for language 'xy'\n"
"    // is '/xy'. Change that to your needs!\n"
"    document.location.href = '/' + lingua + '/';\n"
"    </script>\n"
"    <noscript>\n"
"<p>Please select your preferred language:</p>\n"
"<ul>\n"
"[% FOREACH lingua IN config.linguas %]\n"
"  <li><a href=\"/[% lingua %]/\">[% lingua %]</a></li>\n"
"[% END %]\n"
"</ul>\n"
"    </noscript>\n"
"  </body>\n"
"</html>\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:241
msgid "The above code assumes that you have top-level per-language directories like `/en/`, `/fr/`, and so on. If you choose a different directory layout, you have to change the link targets in lines 40 and 46 accordingly."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:243
msgid "The best solution is to let the server redirect the user to their preferred language. Read on about content negotiation below."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:245
msgid "## Content Negotiation"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:247
msgid "Content negotiation happens when a web server ([nginx](http://www.nginx.com/), [apache](http://httpd.apache.org/), ...) selects the appropriate language version of a piece of content based on the visitor's preference laid forth in their browser language preferences.  See [Simple Content Negotiation for Nginx](http://www.guido-flohr.net/simple-content-negotiation-for-nginx/) for all the gory details of that. Contrary to what the name of the article suggests, it will shed sufficient light on the topic also for users of other web servers than nginx."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:249
msgid "Content negotiation can be made arbitrarily complicated. In practice there is one single valid strategy: A visitor of your start page `http://YOURDOMAIN` should be redirected to the start page in their preferred language and from that moment on they should be pinpointed to that language until they change it. That means that you have to implement content negotiation only for the start page which simplifies things a lot. This is because there is only room for one `/index.html` and the best strategy is to make that just an entry point that brings you to the content in your preferred language."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-configuration.md:251
msgid "Server-side solutions are described at the above mentioned blog post [Simple Content Negotiation for Nginx](http://www.guido-flohr.net/simple-content-negotiation-for-nginx/) but as a fallback and short of better ideas feel free to steal the start page for this site from https://github.com/gflohr/qgoda-site/blob/master/index.html."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:2
msgctxt "title"
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:6
msgctxt "description"
msgid "Overview of Qgoda's Multilanguage and Internationalization (I18N) features"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:8
msgid "Multi-lingualism in Qgoda is an integral, built-in feature mostly built upon easy to follow conventions."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:15
msgid "In a typical website there are two types of translatable content.  You usually have common texts, typically in headers, footers, navigations, sidebars and so on.  Most of the time, these texts come from templates.  And then there is your actual content, your blog posts, articles or other editorial content."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:19
msgid "## Template Texts"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:21
msgid "Common texts in templates are translated with [Template::Plugin::Gettext](https://github.com/gflohr/Template-Plugin-Gettext) an internationalization plug-in for the [Template Toolkit](http://www.template-toolkit.org/)."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:23
msgid "Take the following template snippet as an example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:31
msgid "For an internationalized site you would write instead:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:39
msgid "The English text is simply turned into an argument to a function.  That function returns the translation, when the document is rendered, and it also serves as a marker for translatable strings, so that you can extract them into a `.po` file, a standard format for translations."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:41
msgid "## Editorial Content"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:43
msgid "For content, you have two options which both have their pros and cons."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:45
msgid "### The Simple Approach"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:47
msgid "You can simply copy the documents from the main language into a separate file and translate it. This is a simple approach and usually sufficient, when the document in question rarely changes. A blog post, a news article or similar documents are usually written just once and then never touched again."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:49
msgid "### Advanced Translation Using PO Files"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:51
msgid "Other documents are expected to change frequently. One example is documentation, like the one that you are reading. If you are translating such documents as a whole, no matter whether it is markdown, HTML, Microsoft Word or just plain text, a translator always has to find the differences in the original document and modify the translation accordingly.  This is a tedious and therefore expensive task."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:53
msgid "A much better approach in these cases is to split a document into more manageable smaller chunks. Modern translation frameworks like [GNU Gettext](https://www.gnu.org/software/gettext/) - the system that internationalization with Qgoda is built upon - aids even more in translation by marking the differences to older versions and even allowing machine translations at least as a starting point."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:55
msgid "## Referencing Documents in Specific Languages"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:57
msgid "For listings, you usually want to display documents in one language. You also often want to link to another document in a particular language, most of the time the current one."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:59
msgid "Qgoda allows you to identify a document by arbitrary properties including the language of the document. The details will be explained later in the chapter [@ q.lanchor(name = 'referencing-languages') @]."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:61
msgid "## Translation Workflow"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:63
msgid "Once your site is internationalized you have to get the content translated and to install the translation. The first, initial shot at this is usually simple, also with other systems. But maintaining the site, updating translations after content has changed, adding more languages are tasks that separate the men from the boys."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:65
msgid "The translation workflow for Qgoda is a standard GNU gettext workflow, in other words, the same workflow that is used to internationalize the vast majority of open source software."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:67
msgid "## Getting Started"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/multilanguage-overview.md:69
msgid "The next chapters will guide you through the necessary steps to make your Qgoda site multilanguage. Start with the chapter [@ q.lanchor(name='multilanguage-configuration') @]."
msgstr ""

