#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:2
msgctxt "title"
msgid "Output Location"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:6
msgctxt "description"
msgid "Learn how input locations are translated to output locations in Qgoda."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:8
msgid ""
"Please note that determining the output location for assets differs\n"
"significantly from other systems for example Jekyll.  Whereas in Jekyll you\n"
"normally set the permalink of an asset, in Qgoda you normally set the \n"
"output path and the permalink is computed from the path.  The result is\n"
"very similar but maybe more flexible."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:14
msgid ""
"By default, an asset's location is simply preserved.  That means if you have an\n"
"asset `{srcdir}/assets/images/logo.jpeg` it will be copied to\n"
"`{sitedir}/assets/images/logo.jpeg`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:20
msgid "## Path Translation"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:22
msgid ""
"Processed assets are subject to path translation.  Their relative path to\n"
"the site directory is by default modified.  With the default configuration\n"
"the asset `{srcdir}/pages/en/about-qgoda.htm` would end up as \n"
"`{sitedir}/pages/en/about-qgoda/index.htm` and the markdown input file\n"
"`{srcdir}/posts/en/version-0.2-released.md` would end up as\n"
"`{sitedir}/posts/en/version-0.2-released/index.html`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:29
msgid "For the gory details of the process, let's take the input location \n"
"`{srcdir}/posts/en/version-0.2-released.md` as an example."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:32
msgid "The starting point is the relative path to the source directory\n"
"`/posts/en/version-0.2-released.md` which has the following components:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:35
msgid ""
"<dl>\n"
"  <dt>posts/en</dt>\n"
"  <dd>The directory portion.</dd>\n"
"  <dt>version-0.2-released</dt>\n"
"  <dd>The basename, that is the filename portion without the suffix or suffixes.</dd>\n"
"  <dt>md</dt>\n"
"  <dd>The suffix or filename extension.</dd>\n"
"</dl>"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:44
msgid ""
"By default the output location of a document in Qgoda relative to the \n"
"configured site directory is\n"
"`{directory}/{basename}/{index}.{suffix}`.  The variable `index`\n"
"has the default value \"index\" which is no coincidence but the default value\n"
"used by all common web servers."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:50
msgid "## Suffix Translation"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:52
msgid ""
"Asset processing is triggered by the suffixes of the source file.  The triggers\n"
"are defined in the variable `C:processors.triggers` in the site configuration\n"
"file `P:_config.yaml`.  Look at this excerpt of the Qgoda default configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:56
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"processors:\n"
"    triggers:\n"
"        md: markdown\n"
"        html: html\n"
"        htm: html\n"
"    chains:\n"
"        markdown:\n"
"            modules: [Markdown, HTML]\n"
"            suffix: html\n"
"            wrapper: html\n"
"        html:\n"
"            modules: HTML\n"
"   modules:\n"
"       Markdown: Markdown\n"
"       HTML: Template::Toolkit\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:74
msgid ""
"The suffix `md` triggers the processor chain `markdown`.  This chain\n"
"has configured an output suffix `html`.  The translated filename of the\n"
"output file is therefore not `index.md` but `index.html`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:78
msgid "The processor chain `html` does *not* define an output suffix.  The suffix is \n"
"therefore left untouched."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:81
msgid "## Multiple Suffixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:83
msgid ""
"A filename can have multiple suffixes, for example \n"
"`what-is-qgoda.md.utf8.fr`.  This is useful for content negotiation as\n"
"implemented in the popular Apache web server.  When doing suffix translation,\n"
"Qgoda translates the rightmost suffix.  The example filename would therefore\n"
"be translated into `what-is-qgoda/index.md.utf8.fr`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:89
msgid ""
"It is also important to note that all suffixes are considered for processor \n"
"chain selection.  The rightmost suffix \"wins\".  If you have a filename\n"
"`example.html.md` the markdown processor chain will be selected because\n"
"`md` is right of `html`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:94
msgid "## Gory Details of Suffix Parsing"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:96
msgid ""
"You may have noticed in one the above example the filename \n"
"`version-0.2-released.md` which gets translated into \n"
"`version-0.2-released/index.md`.  Obviously only `md` is considered a suffix\n"
"and `2-released` is not."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:101
msgid ""
"Qgoda's notion of a suffix is a string of one or more alphanumerical\n"
"characters.  Since `2-released` contains a hyphen, it is not considered\n"
"a suffix."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:105
msgid ""
"Suffixes are extracted right to left, stopping at the first false positive.\n"
"Take `version-0.22.beta-released.utf8.en.md` as a rather esoteric example.\n"
"The software would consider `md`, `en`, `utf8` suffixes and stop then\n"
"because `beta-released` contains a non-alphanumerical character.  Although\n"
"`22` (before the string \"beta\") contains only alphanumerical characters\n"
"because the suffix extraction had already stopped."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:112
msgid "## Permalinks"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:114
msgid ""
"Permalinks are computed from the output location.  By default, they are \n"
"simply the relative path to the site directory.  If the filename portion\n"
"of the output location matches the configured index string (normally\n"
"\"index\") followed by one or more suffixes the filename is stripped off."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:119
msgid "For example `posts/en/about-qgoda/index.utf8.md` would be translated into\n"
"the permalink `/posts/en/about-qgoda/`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:122
msgid "## Customization"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:124
msgid ""
"You can fully customize both output location and permalinks by setting the\n"
"variables `C:location` or `C:permalink` respectively in the front matter of an\n"
"asset, as a default for a certain directory or site wide in `C:_config.yaml`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:128
msgid ""
"You can interpolate all kinds of asset variables into the configured string\n"
"by placing them inside {curly} braces.  For example the default configuration\n"
"for the variable `C:location` is `/{directory}/{basename}/{config.index}.{suffix}`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/output-location.md:132
msgid "The following variables are meaningful for location and permalink \n"
"customization:"
msgstr ""

