#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:13
msgid "Lists of search patterns in Qgoda follow the convention of [gitignore](https://git-scm.com/docs/gitignore), only that you put your configuration in a [YAML](http://yaml.org/) file `P:_config.yaml` and not in a file `P:.gitignore`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:17
msgid "As an example we use the configuration variable `C:exclude` which is used for [excluding files from being processed]([@ q.llink(name = 'excluding-files') @])."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:19
msgid "## Special Characters"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:21
msgid "Some characters in patterns have a special meaning."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:23
msgid "### The Star/Asterisk \"*\""
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:25
msgid "The star or asterisk stands for an arbitrary number of characters except for a slash:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:34
msgid "This will exclude all XCF files in the subdirectory `images` for example `images/logo.xcf` but *not* `images/ci/logo.xcf` (because the star/asterisk does not match a slash)."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:36
msgid "Note that `*.xcf` also matches the file `.xcf`.  The star stands for an arbitrary number of characters and that includes zero characters."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:38
msgid "### The Double Star/Asterisk \"**\""
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:40
msgid "Two consecutive stars `**` stand for any sequence of characters including the slash."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:49
msgid "This now matches `images/ci/logo.xcf` *and* `images/logo.xcf` and also `images/nothing/beats/nesting/logo.xcf`.  The pattern `**` matches recursively."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:51
msgid "### The Exclamation Mark \"!\""
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:53
msgid "The exclamation mark negates a pattern.  See [below](#negating-patterns) for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:55 ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:139
msgid ""
"[@ WRAPPER components/infobox.html\n"
"           type = \"warning\" title = \"The exclamation mark is special to YAML\" @]\n"
"The exclamation mark <code>!</code> is a special character in YAML and JSON.  You therefore have to put negated patters into quotes, for example \"!a/b\".\n"
"[@ END @]"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:60
msgid "### The Question Mark \"?\""
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:62
msgid "The question mark standard for any character except for a slash."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/pattern-lists.md:71
msgid "This matches `images/corporate-logos` and `images/corporate_logos` and `images/corporatedQlogos` and `images/corporate&logos`."
msgstr ""

