#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:106
msgid "### Front Matter"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:108
msgid "One question remained: The output file `_site/index.md` is an identical copy of the input file.  But we want it to be converted to HTML, right?"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:110
msgid "That requires a little change to the input file.  Change `index.md` so that it looks like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:112
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"---\n"
"title: My Blog\n"
"---\n"
"This is my first blog created with Qgoda."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:121
msgid "You can replace \"My Blog\" with a \"Jane Appleseed's Cooking Experience\" but you may have guessed that already."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:123
msgid "Qgoda will only run a file through the Markdown processor (*cook* it) if a file starts with three hypens `---`.  Everything up to the next line that contains of just three hyphens is now interpreted as *front matter* in [YAML](http://www.yaml.org/) resp. [JSON](https://www.json.org/) syntax."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:125
msgid "Save the file and something will happen in the terminal window:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:127
msgid ""
"```bash\n"
"[info] start rebuilding site because of file system change\n"
"[info] start building site\n"
"[error][builder] /tmp/qgoda-quickstart/index.md: error reading view '/tmp/qgoda-quickstart/_views/default.html': No such file or directory.\n"
"[error][builder] >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>\n"
"[error][builder] one artefact has not been built because of errors (see above)\n"
"[error][builder] >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>\n"
"[info] finished building site with 0 artefacts\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:137
msgid "Qgoda complains about a missing HTML file.  Why? Because converting Markdown to HTML is almost never enough because that will normally just create an HTML fragment.  A usable HTML document also needs a head with meta information, and some decoration like navigations, a header, a footer and so on."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:139
msgid "So, let's create a minimal HTML wrapper template (called a *view* in Qgoda):"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:141 ../en/docs/qgoda-plug-in.md:14
msgid "[% TAGS [@ @] %]"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:143
msgid ""
"```tt2\n"
"<!doctype html>\n"
"<html>\n"
"  <head>\n"
"    <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n"
"    <title>[% asset.title %]</title>\n"
"  </head>\n"
"  <body>\n"
"    <h1>[% asset.title %]</h1>\n"
"    [% asset.content %]\n"
"  </body>\n"
"</html>\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:157
msgid "Save it as `_views/default.html`.  Qgoda will notice the new file and trigger a re-generation of the site.  Look into the output directory `_site`.  You will see that `_site/index.md` is gone, because Qgoda always cleans up (*prunes*).  But there is a new file `_site/index/index.md`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:159
msgid "Cooked content is subject to [path translation]([@ q.llink(name='output-location') @]).  Qgoda tries to guess a suitable location for the output file, and in the current case that guess was wrong.  Yes, bad start, but you will see that it will get better."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:161
msgid "But the error is simple to fix.  Just edit `index.md` once more:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:163
msgid ""
"```markdown\n"
"---\n"
"title: My Blog\n"
"location: /index.html\n"
"---\n"
"This is my first blog created with Qgoda."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:173
msgid "A quick glance at the output directory `P:_site` shows that the trick worked.  The file is now `_site/index.html`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:175
msgid "Time to look at the file that Qgoda has created:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:177
msgid ""
"<figure class=\"figure w-100\">\n"
"  <img src=\"/images/qgoda-in-15-minutes/processor-chains.svg\"\n"
"       alt=\"Qgoda Processor Chains\">\n"
"  <figcaption class=\"figure-caption text-xs-center\">\n"
"    The view template (left) and the Markdown/YAML content (right) are combined into the output html file (center).\n"
"  </figcaption>\n"
"</figure>"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:185
msgid "By default, Qgoda processes the content in these stages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:187
msgid "1. Front matter (here `title` and `location`) is stripped off and turned into document properties."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:189
msgid "2. The Markdown file is run through the Markdown processor, turning strings like `## Blog Posts` into HTML code (`<h2>Blog Posts</h2>`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:191
msgid "3. The output of the previous step is run through the template processor Template Toolkit.  In the above case there was no template code and that step was unnecessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:193
msgid "4. The *view template* (defaults to `_views/default.html`) gets processed, and the output of steps 2 and 3 above is inserted for `[% asset.content %]`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:195
msgid "It's a slight fib.  Actually the whole process except for step 1 is completely configurable."
msgstr ""

