#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:337
msgid "You know that the new documents are there.  But how can you see them in the browser? You have to create links to them from the start page."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:339
msgid "This is the most complicated part, as it involves  a little programming with the Template Toolkit.  Edit the file `index.md` until it reads like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:341
msgid ""
"```tt2;line-numbers\n"
"---\n"
"title: My Blog\n"
"location: /index.html\n"
"---\n"
"This is my first blog created with Qgoda."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:348
msgid "## Blog Posts"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:350
msgid ""
"[% USE q = Qgoda %]\n"
"<ul>\n"
"[% FOREACH post IN q.list(type = 'recipe').nsortBy('date') %]\n"
"  <li>\n"
"    <h3>[% post.title %]</h3>\n"
"    <p>[% post.excerpt %]</p>\n"
"    <p>\n"
"      <a href=\"[% post.permalink %]\">Read more</a>\n"
"    </p>\n"
"  </li>\n"
"[% END %]\n"
"</ul>\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:364
msgid "The first line that requires an explanation is line 9: `[% USE q = Qgoda %]`.  The <a href=\"http://www.template-toolkit.org/docs/manual/Directives.html#section_USE\"><code>USE</code></a> keyword loads a plug-in for the Template Toolkit, in this case the Qgoda plug-in that ships with Qgoda.  This plug-in lets you access all Qgoda features from within your templates and documents.  By convention, you alias the plug-in with the letter `q`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:366
msgid "The <a href=\"http://www.template-toolkit.org/docs/manual/Directives.html#section_FOREACH\"><code>FOREACH</code></a> keyword iterates over lists.  The list used here is produced by the plug-in method `q.list()` which --- when called without arguments --- gives you all documents that Qgoda knows about."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:368
msgid ""
"[@ WRAPPER components/infobox.html\n"
"             type = 'warning' \n"
"             title = \"Template Code Is Case-Sensitive!\" @]\n"
"You have to write \"FOREACH\" and \"IN\" and not \"foreach\" or \"in\".  You will seldom mis-spell \"FOREACH\" but writing \"in\" instead of \"IN\" is a common mistake that is hard to spot.  Whenever a listing is empty without obvious reason, check your spelling!\n"
"[@ END @]"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:374
msgid "But we want just recipe documents.  Remember that the recipes contained a line `type: recipe` in the YAML front matter? We filter by that property so that only recipes appear in the list."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:376
msgid "Check the result in the browser.  Your recipes should now appear on the start page, sorted by last modification date."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:378
msgid "By the way, you can add more filters to further restrict the list:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:380
msgid ""
"```tt2\n"
"[% q.list(type = 'recipe' lingua = asset.lingua) %]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:384
msgid "This would now only list documents that have a property `V:lingua` with the same value as the current page's `V:lingua`.  The property lingua is used by convention for the language code of a document.  Right now, that would lead to an empty list, because we didn't use the property `V:lingua`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:386
msgid "### Links"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:388
msgid "Sometimes, you want to link to a particular document.  Imagine, you want to recommend a cherry tart as a dessert to the hard-boiled egg.  You can, of course do this in `hard-boiled-egg.md`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:390
msgid ""
"```;markdown\n"
"---\n"
"title: Hard Boiled Egg\n"
"name: hard-boiled egg\n"
"type: recipe\n"
"---\n"
"## Ingredients"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:403
msgid ""
"1. Put the egg in the water.\n"
"2. Bring the water to boil.\n"
"3. Turn off the heat and wait 12 minutes."
