#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:410
msgid "The syntax `[LABEL](href)` is used for links in Markdown.  Hard-coding links like this works perfectly, and if you like to keep it simple, just stick with it."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:412
msgid "The disadvantage is that the link will be broken, if you decide to rename the cherry tart recipe, for example from `cherry-tart.md` to `cherry-on-the-tart.md`.  You can prevent that by using \"symbolic\" links.  By convention, you use the property `V:name` to identify a document independently of its concrete location.  Since we had given the `V:name` `cherry-tart` to the cherry tart recipe, you can write:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:414
msgid ""
"```tt2\n"
"[% USE q = Qgoda %]\n"
"Recommendation for dessert:\n"
"[Cherry Tart]([% q.link(name = 'cherry-tart') %])\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:420
msgid "That produces the same link as before but the link will now stay intact if you decide to relocate the cherry tart recipe."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/qgoda-in-15-minutes.md:422
msgid ""
