#: ../en/docs/table-of-contents.md:95
msgid "The table of contents generation is implemented as a <q-term>HTMLFilter</q-term> plug-in.  That means it is executed at the very end of the rendering process."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/table-of-contents.md:97
msgid "### Internal Logic"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/table-of-contents.md:99
msgid "The plug-in finds all `<h2>` to `<h6>` elements and generates a hierarchy from the tags found.  It is quite strict.  For example, an `<h4>` tag after an `<h3>` tag is ignored because the hierarchy level `<h3>` is missing."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/table-of-contents.md:101
msgid "It collects the document structure and passes it in the variable `V:asset.toc` to the plug-in that renders the table of contents.  See the source code of the auto-generated default templates `_views/components/toc.html` and `_views/components/toc/level.html` for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/table-of-contents.md:103
msgid "Inside all `<h2>` to `<h6>` elements that have been recognized a named anchor `<a id=\"SLUG\" name=\"SLUG\" href=\"#\">` is inserted, where `SLUG` is the <q-term>slugified:slug</q-term> text inside of the headline element.  These named anchors are the targets of the links in the rendered table of contents."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/table-of-contents.md:105
msgid "### Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/table-of-contents.md:107
msgid "Since it is an HTMLFilter plug-in, you configure it in the options for the plug-in.  The command `qgoda config` should print something like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/table-of-contents.md:109
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"  options:\n"
"    HTMLFilter:\n"
"    - AnchorTarget\n"
"    - Generator\n"
"    - CleanUp\n"
"    - - TOC\n"
"      - content_tag\n"
"      - qgoda-content\n"
"      - toc_tag\n"
"      - qgoda-toc\n"
"      - start\n"
"      - 2\n"
"      - end\n"
"      - 6\n"
"      - template\n"
"      - components/toc.html\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/table-of-contents.md:128
msgid "A more readable but equivalent form would look like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/table-of-contents.md:130
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"  options:\n"
"    HTMLFilter:\n"
"    - AnchorTarget\n"
"    - Generator\n"
"    - CleanUp\n"
"    - [TOC,\n"
"       content_tag, qgoda-content,\n"
"       toc_tag, qgoda-toc\n"
"       start, 2,\n"
"       end, 6,\n"
"       template, components/toc.html] \n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/table-of-contents.md:144
msgid "The configuration variables are passed as key-value pairs.  Their meaning is as follows:"
