#: ../en/docs/taxonomies.md:2
msgctxt "title"
msgid "Taxonomies"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/taxonomies.md:6
msgctxt "description"
msgid "Taxonomies partition your site according to arbitrary aspects."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/taxonomies.md:8
msgid ""
"Taxonomies group assets into groups sharing common properties.  Qgoda supports\n"
"an arbitrary number of taxonomies.  Every asset property can be promoted to a \n"
"taxonomy, simply by using it as a taxonomy."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/taxonomies.md:12
msgid "The concept of taxonomies is best understood by a typical example.  Consider\n"
"a document with the following front matter:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/taxonomies.md:15
msgid ""
"```yaml\n"
"---\n"
"title: Qgoda Pygments Plug-In\n"
"lingua: en\n"
"tags:\n"
"  - Syntax Highlighting\n"
"  - Plug-Ins\n"
"  - Python \n"
"  - Qgoda\n"
"categories: Development\n"
"---\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/taxonomies.md:28
msgid ""
"Three default taxonomies are used here, `lingua`, `tags`, and `categories`.\n"
"By convention, taxonomies that are typically single-valued use the singular\n"
"(for example `lingua` because a document can be written in only one\n"
"language), taxonomies that can have multiple values usually use the\n"
"plural form."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/taxonomies.md:34
msgid ""
"Taxonomies allow you to partition or divide your web site into groups of\n"
"related documents.  For example, you can identify all English documents\n"
"with the condition `lingua=\"en\"`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/taxonomies.md:38
msgid ""
"<figure class=\"figure w-100\">\n"
"  <img src=\"/images/taxonomies/taxonomy-lingua.svg\"\n"
"       class=\"large-image figure-img img-fluid img-rounded d-block m-x-auto\"\n"
"       alt=\"All assets/documents with lingua 'en' establish a group of documents.\" />\n"
"  <figcaption class=\"figure-caption text-xs-center\">\n"
"    All English documents.\n"
"  </figcaption>\n"
"</figure>"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/taxonomies.md:47
msgid "Likewise, you can identify all documents that are tagged with \"Qgoda\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/taxonomies.md:49
msgid ""
"<figure class=\"figure w-100\">\n"
"  <img src=\"/images/taxonomies/taxonomy-tags.svg\"\n"
"       class=\"large-image figure-img img-fluid img-rounded d-block m-x-auto\"\n"
"       alt=\"You can also group all documents tagged with &quot;Qgoda&quot; and &quot;Plug-Ins&quot;.\" />\n"
"  <figcaption class=\"figure-caption text-xs-center\">\n"
"    All documents tagged with \"Qgoda\". \n"
"  </figcaption>\n"
"</figure>"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/taxonomies.md:58
msgid ""
"By combining taxonomies you can define arbitrary subsets of a site's documents.\n"
"You can for example identify all English documents tagged with \"Qgoda\" and\n"
"\"Plug-Ins\" by `AND`'-ing the two above conditions."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/taxonomies.md:62
msgid ""
"<figure class=\"figure w-100\">\n"
"  <img src=\"/images/taxonomies/taxonomies-combined.svg\"\n"
"       class=\"large-image figure-img img-fluid img-rounded d-block m-x-auto\"\n"
"       alt=\"Combining taxonomies can create arbitrary partitions of a site.\" />\n"
"  <figcaption class=\"figure-caption text-xs-center\">\n"
"    All English documents tagged with \"Qgoda\".\n"
"  </figcaption>\n"
"</figure>"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/template-variables.md:2
msgctxt "title"
msgid "Template Variables"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/template-variables.md:6
msgctxt "description"
msgid "Standard and Pre-Defined Template Variables"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/template-variables.md:8
msgid ""
"[% USE q = Qgoda %]\n"
"[% PROCESS \"functions/css-modules.tt\" %]\n"
"Not all of the following variables are necessarily available everywhere.\n"
"Many of them like `V:asset.name` are mere conventions."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/template-variables.md:13
msgid ""
"Qgoda passes all template variables inside the <q-term>hash:hashes</q-term> (resp. \n"
"<q-term>object:objects</q-term> if\n"
"you prefer that term) `V:asset` and `V:config`.  All other\n"
"variables, especially top-level variables are free for your use."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/template-variables.md:18
msgid ""
"[% WRAPPER components/infobox.html\n"
"   type=\"warning\" title='Overwriting Internal Variables' %]\n"
"Qgoda allows overwriting these internal variables which may also affect\n"
"documents processed afterwards.  This feature can lead to interesting\n"
"results if you know what you are doing.  In general, it is a recipe\n"
"for trouble.\n"
"[%- END %]"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/template-variables.md:26
msgid ""
"[% WRAPPER \"components/template-variable.html\"\n"
"   variable=\"asset\" type=\"hash\" %]\n"
"The variable `asset` is the container for all variables specific to\n"
"the asset currently being processed.\n"
"[%- END %]"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/template-variables.md:32
msgid ""
"[% WRAPPER \"components/template-variable.html\"\n"
"   variable=\"asset.draft\" type=\"boolean (0 or 1)\" %]\n"
"Set to a truth value (for example 1 if the document is a draft.  Drafts only get processed when the command-line option [% q.llink(name = 'command-line-interface') %] `-D` or `--drafts` was specified.\n"
"[%- END %]"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/template-variables.md:37
msgid ""
"[% WRAPPER \"components/template-variable.html\"\n"
"   variable=\"asset.lingua\" type=\"RFC4647 language identifier\" %]\n"
"An identifier of the language of the document. You should use a language identifier that conforms to <a href=\"https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc4647.txt\">RFC4647</a>, something like \"en\", \"en-us\", or \"fr-ca\". It is strongly recommended that you stick to the variable name `lingua` because this convention is built into Qgoda at many places.\n"
"[%- END %]"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/template-variables.md:42
msgid ""
"[% WRAPPER \"components/template-variable.html\"\n"
"   variable=\"asset.priority\" type=\"integer\" %]\n"
"All artifacts are built sorted by their priority.  A higher value means that they are generated first.  Normally, you should assign a low priority, for example -999 to listings so that they are generated after other pages and can access all of their data.\n"
"[%- END %]"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/template-variables.md:47
msgid ""
"[% WRAPPER \"components/template-variable.html\"\n"
"   variable=\"asset.virtual\" type=\"boolean (0 or 1)\" %]\n"
"Virtual documents to not get published, to be more exact, they do not go through the second pass of processing (the HTML wrapping) and hence are not written to disk.\n"
"[%- END %]"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/template-variables.md:52
msgid ""
"[% WRAPPER \"components/template-variable.html\"\n"
"   variable=\"config\" type=\"hash\" %]\n"
"`config` gives you access to the site configuration from `P:_config.yaml`.\n"
"The configuration variable `C:paths.views` in `P:_config.yaml` is\n"
"accessible from a template as `config.paths.views`.  See\n"
"[% q.lanchor(name='configuration-variables') %] for a complete list.\n"
"[%- END %]"
msgstr ""

