#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:2
msgctxt "title"
msgid "Translating Templates"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:6
msgctxt "description"
msgid "How to get text inside templates translated"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:8
msgid "Internationalizing Template Toolkit templates is very easy with the help of the module [`Template-Plugin-Gettext`](https://github.com/gflohr/Template-Plugin-Gettext)."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:12
msgid "## Activating the Plug-In"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:14
msgid "Before you can use translation functions, you have to activate the plug-in:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:16
msgid ""
"[% USE q = Qgoda %]\n"
"[% TAGS [@ @] %]\n"
"```tt2\n"
"[% USE gtx = Gettext('com.example.www', asset.lingua) %]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:22
msgid "This is done with the `USE` directive which takes two arguments. the The first argument is the so-called *textdomain*, an arbitrary string identifying your translation database.  The second one is the language of the file.  This is usually stored in the document property `V:lingua`."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:24
msgid "Since you must always store your textdomain in the configuration variable `C:po.textdomain`, you can use the value of that variable instead of hard-coding the textdomain:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:26
msgid ""
"```tt2\n"
"[% USE gtx = Gettext(config.po.textdomain, asset.lingua) %]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:30
msgid "Now you can easily change the textdomain without touching every template."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:32
msgid "## Translating Strings"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:34
msgid "### Constant Strings"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:36
msgid "Strings are translated by passing them to the template function `gtx.gettext()`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:38
msgid ""
"```tt2\n"
"<h1>[% gtx.gettext('Welcome to My Site') %]</h1>\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:42
msgid "When rendering, the function returns the translation for the string or the original string, when there is no translation for it. But it also serves as a marker, that is later used to extract all translatable strings so that they can be sent to translators."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:44
msgid "If you prefer, you can also use Template Toolkit filters for translation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:46
msgid ""
"```tt2\n"
"<h1>[% 'Welcome to My Site' | gettext %]</h1>\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:50
msgid "This does exactly the same."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:52
msgid "### Variable Strings"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:54
msgid "Sometimes strings contain variable parts:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:56
msgid ""
"```tt2\n"
"<small>Written by [% asset.author %] ([% asset.organization %])</small>\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:60
msgid "The recommended way to translate such strings uses the function `gtx.xgettext()`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:62
msgid ""
"```tt2\n"
"<small>[% gtx.xgettext('Written by {author} ({organization})',\n"
"                       author = asset.author\n"
"                       organization = asset.organization) %]</small>\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:68
msgid "You use placeholders for the variable part, and pass the value for each placeholder as named arguments to the function. Placeholders can be arbitrary identifiers."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:70
msgid "### Plural Forms"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:72
msgid "Languages largely differ in the way they handle plural forms and strings. If a string contains a (cardinal) number you should try to help translators by using the specialized plural function `gtx.nxgettext()`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:74
msgid ""
"```tt2\n"
"<em>[% gtx.ngettext('One comment', '{num} comments', \n"
"                    asset.num_comments,\n"
"                    num = asset.num_comments) %]</em>\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:80
msgid "The first argument is the singular form of the string, the second one is the plural form. The third argument is the number of items used (so that the function can pick the correct plural form for a particular language)."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:82
msgid "The other arguments are the values for the placeholder(s) used."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:84
msgid "Yes, this is a little bit tedious but still as simple as this problem can probably be solved. You might think, why not just use an `IF` clause?"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:86
msgid ""
"```tt2\n"
"[% IF assset.num_comments == 1 %]\n"
"<em>[% gtx.gettext('One comment') %]</em>\n"
"[% ELSE %]\n"
"<em>[% gtx.xgettext('{num} comments', \n"
"                    num = asset.num_comments) %]</em>\n"
"[% ENDIF %]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:95
msgid "That will in fact work for a number of languages but for example for Russian your translator will contact you and tell you that it cannot be accurately translated."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:97
msgid "### Other Variants"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:99
msgid "There are a lot more variants of the translation functions, for example strings containing plural forms. See the [documentation for the Gettext plugin](https://github.com/gflohr/Template-Plugin-Gettext) and its [API documentation](https://github.com/gflohr/Template-Plugin-Gettext/blob/master/lib/Template/Plugin/Gettext.pod#user-content-FUNCTIONS) for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:101
msgid "## Complicated Strings"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:103
msgid "One golden rule in (software) internationalization is: Do not assemble strings!"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:105
msgid "Do *not* do this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:107
msgid ""
"```tt2\n"
"[% gtx.gettext('See the documentation at') %]\n"
"<a href=\"http://www.a.com/\">A</a>\n"
"[% gtx.gettext('and') %]\n"
"<a href=\"http://www.b.com/\">B</a>\n"
"[% gtx.gettext('for more information!') %]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:115
msgid "This gives your translators a hard time, and sometimes it will not be possible at all to translate such constructs into a particular language."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:117
msgid "Do this instead:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:119
msgid ""
"```tt2\n"
"[% xgettext('See the documentation at <a href=\"{link1}\">A</a>\n"
"             or <a href=\"{link2}\">B</a> for more information!',\n"
"            link1 = 'http://www.a.com',\n"
"            link2 = 'http://www.b.com') %]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:134
msgid "## Troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translating-templates.md:136
msgid "A very common problem is that `gtx.gettext()` seems to return an empty string. The reason is almost always that you have forgotten to activate the `Gettext` plug-in. See [above](#activating-the-plug-in) how to fix that."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:2
msgctxt "title"
msgid "Translation Workflow"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:6
msgctxt "description"
msgid "Creating translation catalogs, translating and updating them."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:8
msgid ""
"Somehow translating something from language into another by software and some\n"
"kind of translation database is a trivial thing. This is the reason why there\n"
"are countless translation frameworks out there."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:12
msgid "Almost all of them have at least one of two common problems:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:14
msgid ""
"* They ignore that translatable strings should be automatically extracted from\n"
"source code. But copying strings manually into a translation file is a tedious\n"
"and errorprone task.\n"
"* Source code, be it programming code or the markdown code of your blog posts\n"
"may change over time. Whenever the original is touched, you want to apply these\n"
"changes with minimal effort to the other language variants. You certainly\n"
"don't want to start with the translation from scratch, neither for the entire\n"
"project or a particular string."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:23
msgid ""
"Qgoda's internationalization (i18n) is based on\n"
"[GNU gettext](https://www.gnu.org/software/gettext/). GNU gettext is the\n"
"de-facto standard for translating free and open-source software, and it\n"
"really shines by its set of mature tools that automate the task of\n"
"translation management to the extent possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:29
msgid ""
"If you want to dig deeper into the topic or if something is unclear, you can\n"
"always consult the [GNU gettext documentation](https://www.gnu.org/software/gettext/manual/gettext.html)\n"
"for the \"big picture\". This page covers mostly the qgoda-specific topics\n"
"only. But it should be enough to get you started."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:36
msgid "[% USE q = Qgoda %]\n"
"[% TAGS [@ @] %]"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:39
msgid "## Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:41
msgid "### GNU Gettext"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:43
msgid ""
"Since Qgoda's internationalization is based on\n"
"[GNU gettext](https://www.gnu.org/software/gettext/) you have to install\n"
"it first. GNU gettext is available for every platform, including Microsoft\n"
"Windows. But it is often split up into two packages \"gettext-runtime\" and\n"
"\"gettext-tools\". Make sure that you install \"gettext-tools\" which contains\n"
"the necessary tools."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:50
msgid "### Git"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:52
msgid "You also need [git](https://git-scm.com/). Git is available on all platforms."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:54
msgid "### Minimal Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:56
msgid ""
"It is also assumed that you have read the chapters \n"
"[@ q.lanchor(name='multilanguage-configuration') @] and\n"
"[@ q.lanchor(name='translating-templates') @] so that there is something to\n"
"translate."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:61
msgid "The minimal configuration you need are the variables `C:linguas` and\n"
"`C:po.textdomain`. Put something like this into `P:_config.yaml`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:64
msgid ""
"```yaml;line-numbers\n"
"linguas:\n"
"    - en\n"
"    - de\n"
"    - fr\n"
"po:\n"
"    textdomain: com.your-site.www\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:73
msgid ""
"The order of languages (line 1) matters! The first one is the default language\n"
"of your site. If you want to follow the examples on this page, make sure that\n"
"`C:linguas` contains at least two languages, one for your default language and\n"
"at least one that can contribute translations."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:78
msgid "The textdomain is not really important. You can pretty much pick any identifier\n"
"you want."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:81
msgid "## The `po` Sub-Command"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:83
msgid "Most tasks are done with the sub-command `qgoda po`. Try `qgoda po --help`\n"
"for a reference."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:86
msgid ""
"Please note that you have to run the command `qgoda po` from the top-level\n"
"directory of your site! Failure to do so will usually result in an error\n"
"message \"configuration variable “po.textdomain” not set\" (because Qgoda cannot\n"
"find your configuration)."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:91
msgid "## Stages Of the Workflow"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:93
msgid ""
"The translation workflow consists of several steps.  You can perform the \n"
"steps individually (that is described below) or you all at once with the\n"
"command `qgoda po all`, which will do all necessary steps at once.  This\n"
"will usually result in some unnecessary actions but is easier to remember"
