#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:230
msgid "### Updating Translations"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:232
msgid "When strings are added or modified, the translations have to be updated.\n"
"That requires the following steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:235
msgid ""
"* a new `POTFILES` that contains the updated list of source files\n"
"* a new `.pot` file that contains the new set of translatable strings\n"
"* mergint the `.pot` file into the existing `.po` translation files with the\n"
"  command `msgmerge`"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:240
msgid "This is done with `qgoda po update-po`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:242
msgid ""
"```bash\n"
"$ qgoda po update-po\n"
"[info][config] reading configuration from '_config.yaml'\n"
"[info] merging de.po\n"
"[info] rename “de.po” to “de.old.po”\n"
"[info] execute: msgmerge de.old.po com.example.www.pot --previous -o de.po\n"
". done.\n"
"[info] unlink “de.old.po”\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:252
msgid ""
"When you have more content to translate this may take considerable time \n"
"because `msgmerge` is trying to do the merge in a smart manner so that you\n"
"don't lose existing translations."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:256
msgid "After this step, your translation files are up-to-date and can be translated."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:258
msgid "### Translating the `.po` Files"
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:260
msgid ""
"The `.po` format is accepted by many professional translators. If you want\n"
"to translate the file yourself, do not use your normal text editor (unless\n"
"it is emacs) but use a specialized tool for it. Search the web for \"PO\n"
"Editor\" and you will find a number of free programs."
msgstr ""

#: ../en/docs/translation-workflow.md:265
msgid "For now, just open the `.po` file in your editor. You will see lots of \n"
"entries like this:"
